5100.name: Sedna Town Square
5100.description:
This is the town square. It is where most of the important meetings take
place as well as just a normal meeting ground. You can find something
always happening here. As you around you see a [sign] in the middle of
the town square.

exdescs.plaque:
----------------------------------------------------------------------
This is the Zany institude of the Demented!!

It has been around for years teaching people how to play Njata.
People have come from all over to play. but before you can
continue you need to know everything the game has to offer.
so continue on to learn how to leave this place.
----------------------------------------------------------------------
exdescs.sign:
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Welcome traveler to the town of Sedna!! You will find that we have
everything you will ever need. If you need a drink The Bear's Paw
Tavern to your right will do the trick. Want another weapon or maybe
some better armor? Edwin the Carpenter will be your best bet to the north
In need of some kind of container to hold more things or want some more
shiny things? Roman the Bronze-smith to the west would be your guy.
Need a letter sent? Then Catherine the Courier would who you want to
talk to south from here. She will get it in there in no time

May your time spent here be a merry one!!!
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

5101.name: Outskirts of Sedna
5101.description:
You have just entered  the town of Sedna via the southern road. It is a
busy town, though mostly only because of mercantile traffic. The town
is built around a small, pristine pond. The town is known for being a
little superstitious. You can get basic protection spells from the local
tavern.

5102.name: Road South of Sedna
5102.description:
You have just entered  the town of Sedna via the southern road. It is a
busy town, though mostly only because of mercantile traffic. The town
is built around a small, pristine pond. The town is known for being a
little superstitious. You can get basic protection spells from the local
tavern.

5103.name: Courier
5103.description:
This is the shack of Catherine the local Courier. She delivers mail all
over the place. If you want something sent she will make sure that it
gets to it's destination in one piece in a timely manner. Which is that it
gets there at all! As you can see she is not in at the moment. Probably
out making a delivery. There is a  [sign] on the door.

5104.name: Commonroom of Bear's Paw Tavern
5104.description:
You have just entered the Bear's Paw Tavern. Something is always going
on here. Whether it be people trying to show off how strong they are. Or
how much liquor they can drink. You will always find the locals in here
You will also find a table of poker going on. Though a lot of people have
seemed to be less interested in it do to people cheating with magic. Or
being accused of doing so. The next room to the East, is where the bar
is for you to order from as well as a staircase to the rooms above.
The tavern has a log cabin type feel to it.

5105.name: Bear's Paw Tavern
5105.description:
This here is the bar. You can order all kinds of drinks as well
as some nice home cooked meal. Just tell the bartender what it
is you want. If  you head upstairs, you can rent a room as well as for the
superstitious get buy some potions of protection up there as well. The tavern
has
a log cabin type feel to it.

5106.name: Bear's Paw Tavern
5106.description:
This is the common room. It's where all the towns people congregate
into to drink their favorite beverage or eat their favorite meal. And catch
up on the local rumors as well as the current events. The room itself is
a large room made out of wood it has a log cabin type feel to it.

5107.name: Bear's Paw Tavern
5107.description:
This is the common room. It's where all the towns people congregate
into to drink their favorite beverage or eat their favorite meal. And catch
up on the local rumors as well as the current events. The room itself is
a large room made out of wood it has a log cabin type feel to it.

5108.name: Path Around the Pond
5108.description:
The pond is surrounded by a lush wooded walk way. You can go
around the entire town without ever having to get off it.  It is the only
 means to get from one side of the town to the other when walking.

5109.name: Sedna Pond
5109.description:
This extremely clear pond is safe to drink from and swim in, and is
regarded with a mix of fear and relief. It is a wellspring of freshwater,
on which the villagers rely on. There are rumors going around that
something supernatural has been happening to the pond. Some say
that it only happens on a full moon just as it's rising once ever three
months. Others say that it happens once every two. The one thing
that everyone agrees on is that what ever it is it's coming from the pond
itself.

5123.name: Under Sedna Pond
5123.description:
You have just dived beneath the water of the pond. Unfortunately all
you can see around you the blue water that surrounds you. You notice
that you are not quite sure which direction to go in.

5124.name: Under Sedna Pond

5127.name: Under Sedna Pond
5127.description:
You have just found the enterce to the cave. Do you go forth or do you decide
to stay outside. The choice is your and yours alone. good luck

As you look around you notice that for some reason the entrance to the cave
doesn't seem to be filling with water. Like there is some sort of magical
barrier that is preventing water from entering.

5128.name: Underground Labyrinth
5128.description:
Welcome to section one of the Underground Labyrinth. As you enter
this section you notice that the water just seems to stop at the entrance.
As if there was a magical barrier stopping the water. You also notice
that it is really dry in here. As you look around it appears that there
is something ever odd about this place. But, you can't seem put your
finger on it, (hypothetically of course!). You also see a  [plaque]  on the
wall.

exdescs.plaque:
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Welcome to the Underground Labyrinth!!.

This is the first section. Can you make it out alive?
This plaque was put up to let you know that you went backwards!!!
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

5140.name: Carpenter
5140.description:
The is the shop of Edwin. He is a Master Carpenter. He is known
for making sophisticated while still being practical weapons and
armor. As you enter the shop you see  [staffs] ,  [spears,]  and other
 types of weapons made out of wood lining the walls.  [Bolts]  and
 [arrows]  on his desk. As well as various pieces of  [leather]  armor
 hanging on the wall.

exdescs.arrow:
these intricate pieces of art work are very elegant and incredible useful
they are long slender pieces of intricate wood. With really elegant
feathers on them.
exdescs.bolt: These tiny pieces maybe small but they pack a mean punch.
exdescs.leather:
These bad boys are the lesser of his craftsmanship. Very durable and
functional. These things don't have as nice a look as the rest of the stuff
he makes.
exdescs.spear:
Same as the staff 6' long and 3 in diameter it also have a 1'  long spear
head on it.
exdescs.staff:
A long single piece of wood who's length is 6'0 and 3 in diameter. It
has a rugged look to it like it can take a beating and last forever.

5141.name: Bronzeworker's Shop
5141.description:
This is the shop of Rowan. He is the best at making really intricate pieces
of art out of bronze. As you enter the shop you see a slew of bronze pieces
hanging from the wall. Sitting on the floor and covering the top of his desk.
Such, wonderful useful things like a highly decorated  [cup].  A set of
shinny  [horse shoes],  a slew of  [pots]  on the wall. A bunch of  [plates]
and [utensils] litter the floor. There is also [jewelery] of all kinds on his
desk. He stairs at you with intent waiting to see what it is you want to buy.

exdescs.cup:
&YThis is an incredibly fancy cup, that has an intricate design. and is gem
incrusted.
exdescs.horse: &YThis a set of very durable and shiny horse shoes.
exdescs.jewelery:
&YA bunch of various fancy looking jewelry very from rings to bracelets
and every thing else you can think of.
exdescs.plates:
&Ythe Plates you are looking at have a nice red circle going around the
edge of them. As well as, a picture of a sun setting in the middle of them.
exdescs.pots: &YThis a set very strong but bland looking pots
exdescs.shoes: &YThis a set of very durable and shiny horse shoes.
exdescs.utensils: &YA set of dull unpolished utensils of various usage.

5142.name: Abandoned Shack
5142.description:
This is a dilapidated building. No ones knows why it's still here or
what it was ever used for in the first place. It's just an old falling
apart building that people refuse to take down for fear of the unknown.

5143.name: Inn Common Room
5143.description:
After going upstairs. You enter into the common area. The rooms are
numbered 1 through 3 going in the pattern of n, e, w. this place is bland
with nothing really to look at other then the three inn room doors. To
rent an inn room, tell Colman which room you'd like to rent. e.g [sayto
colman rent room one] would allow you to rent the north inn room.

5144.name: Inn Room #1
5144.description:
This is one of three inn rooms. They are all the same. There is a bed in
the far corner and nothing else. It makes a perfect place to sleep and
store stuff for a short time. Just remember to take all your stuff before
you leave. Because you never know who might get the room after you.

this section you notice that the water just seems to stop at the entrance.
As if there was a magical barrier stopping the water. You also notice
that it is really dry in here. As you look around it appears that there
is something ever odd about this place. But, you can't seem put your
finger on it, (hypothetically of course!).

is also hidden behind a maze... But from what you can see it seems easier
then the last ones you had to do... The walls are also painted yellow in here.

5187.name: Treasure Room
5187.description:
You have Finally found the Treasure Room. It covered from head to toe
with gold as far as the eye can see. The room is also filled with chests. That
seem to be here just for you.

5188.name: Underground Labyrinth
5188.description:
This is the room of the vial monster who has decided to call the the
Labyrinth home upon entering you see that this room is more elaborate
then any other room in the dungeon. There is a bright red  [rug]  lying on
the floor as well as  [paintings]  lining the wall. Which for some reason
this room was kept pristine without a single spec of dust on anything..
which for all accounts is completely unexplainable. You also see a  [plaque] on
the wall.

exdescs.painting:
As you look at the paiting you notice that they are portraits of some fancy
magic users. As you look closer at one you also get the feeling that the eyes
are actually moving with you
exdescs.plaque:

and you are home free. Also if you are wondering the treasure room isn't
here. It's located some place else. uhG! AnOther choicE Another blaSted
paTh to the treasure room. Hopefully you can find it before you leave.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

5189.name: Underground Labyrinth
5189.description:
This is the last room in the dungeon. You can use the key you got off the
monster you just defeated. It will take you back to the Village of Sedna.
Upon entering you see that this room is more elaborate then any other room
in the dungeon. There is a bright red  [rug]  lying on the floor as well as
[paintings]  lining the wall. Which for some reason this room was kept
pristine without a single spec of dust on anything..Which for all accounts is
completely unexplainable... For Some reason it appears as tho this room and
the last are identical.
